Your first day or so\
- the first day is awkward\
- you feel like a lost puppy and will weirdly smile at everyone and they will weirdly smile back at you\
- include yourself in EVERYTHING, the team will probably invite you out to lunch with them, go go go, getting acquainted with the team is your new goal\
- be open minded and soak in as much info as you can but recognize you may not know everything and that's ok - don't be a know-it-all\
- your first few months are all about learning and doing whatever it takes to establish yourself\
- it's also ok to say no or push back on deadlines if you feel they are unrealistic - if something is going to take you 20 hours and there are only 8 hours in a working day and you have 1 day to do it, try to work out expectations for the looming deadline and not loose your mind\
\
\
What I wish someone had told me when I started\
- the industry isn't like mad men\
- free over-time is not ok\
- it's ok to negotiate salary and vacay\
- all of the agencies in london talk, be careful\
- networking is actually important\
- freelance can suck but it's a great place to practice skills\
- your first job doesn't have to be forever\
- find someone in the industry you can trust - mentor, prof, friend\
- take time for yourself and your friends/family - devil wears prada\
